replies.bodyText: In case the profile specified a canonical with a version, I used the same split as done in CodeGenerator to just compare the URL part.
replies.author: tbieste

timeline.bodyText: seems a bit odd not to handle the element.is(Uri.class) in the if/else block with the others, but I suppose its fine
timeline.author: lmsurpre

replies.bodyText: I kept the same if/else logic as used in the apply(...) method (around line 121) for expanded value sets to be consistent.  I can change both places if there's a way that would be better.
replies.author: tbieste

timeline.bodyText:
maybe just combine it with the method above and take an Element?
then you just need one if/else block, right?  maybe a "horse apiece" though.
timeline.author: lmsurpre

replies.bodyText: Yeah, I went back and forth on that.  My goal was to minimize the number of lines of code to be added for any future syntax-based value sets (e.g. UCUM), so I thought this ended up looking cleaner.
replies.author: tbieste

timeline.bodyText: I wonder if one of these should include the word MaxValueSet or ConstraintGenerator to make it clear what the test is for
timeline.author: lmsurpre

replies.bodyText: Good call.  I'll rename these to be more descriptive.
replies.author: tbieste

timeline.bodyText: this comment was very helpful for me, thanks
timeline.author: lmsurpre
